Privacy Policy:

At NFTLegitimateDAO Chainlink APP, we are committed to protecting the privacy and confidentiality of our users. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard the data obtained from Facebook users for the sole purpose of user verification. Please read this policy carefully to understand our practices regarding your data and how we handle it.

1. Data Collection and Usage:
   a. Verification Purpose: We collect and process the first post content of a user from their Facebook profile solely for the purpose of user authentication during the enrollment process.
   b. No Data Storage: We do not store any user data, including the first post content, in our systems, blockchain, or databases. Once the user's data has been processed for verification, it is immediately discarded.

2. Consent:
   By using our service and voluntarily providing us access to your Facebook account, you consent to the collection and use of your first post content solely for user verification purposes as outlined in this Privacy Policy.

3. Data Security:
   a. We take reasonable measures to protect the confidentiality and integrity of the data collected. However, please note that no method of data transmission or storage can guarantee absolute security.
   b. We do not share, sell, or transfer any user data obtained from Facebook to any third parties.

4. Compliance with Laws:
   a. We comply with all applicable laws and regulations governing the collection, use, and protection of user data.
   b. In the event that we receive a lawful request for user data from a government authority, we may be obligated to disclose the data.

5. Children's Privacy:
   Our services are not intended for individuals under the age of [minimum age]. We do not knowingly collect personal information from individuals under this age. If we become aware of any such data being collected, we will promptly delete it from our systems.

6. Changes to the Privacy Policy:
   We reserve the right to update or modify this Privacy Policy at any time. Any changes will be effective immediately upon posting the updated policy on our website or app. It is your responsibility to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any updates or modifications.

7. Contact Us:
   If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or the handling of your data, please contact us at [contact email or address].

By using our services, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy and agree to the collection and use of your data for the sole purpose of user verification as described above.
